An example

From an ImageId we get the pixel coordinates or the mask for every defect. Here an example of steel image.

{% raw %} 
img_id = train["ImageId"][101]
img_path = train_path / img_id
im = Image.open(img_path)
im
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
height, width = im.shape
height, width

(256, 1600)
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
assert height == 256
assert width == 1600
{% endraw %}

Discovery defect functions

{% raw %}

defeat_position[source]

defeat_position()

Get coordinates of defects (x, y) given an ImageId and a ClassId

Attributes

img_id: str ImageId in df, image name with suffix

class_id: int ClassId in df, type of defect

df: pd.DataFrame default train

Returns

x : np.ndarray

y : np.ndarray

{% endraw %} {% raw %}
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
x,y = defeat_position(img_id='bca4ae758.jpg', class_id=1)
x.shape, y.shape

((2839,), (2839,))
